{"pageProps":{"post":{"creator":"Marc Reid","title":"Creating Multiple Axes without Duplicating Marks","link":"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/","pubDate":"Mon, 26 Sep 2022 16:14:12 +0000","content:encoded":"\n<p>Tableau always places the axis for a single measure on the left of the chart and then on the bottom of the chart for a second measure, such as in a scatter plot. Sometimes, however, it makes more sense to have these axes on the opposite side of the chart to help readability.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Jon Schwabish highlighted this point in the below tweet, referencing a Bloomberg chart showing the axis on the right-hand side:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"embed-twitter\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">You know, I&#39;m starting to wonder why we don&#39;t put more vertical axes on the *right side* of our graphs? That&#39;s where we are usually trying to direct people&#39;s attention, right? (this graph from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/BBGVisualData?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@BBGVisualData</a>) <a href=\"https://t.co/G4BwAP9ZGQ\">https://t.co/G4BwAP9ZGQ</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/a6s4WbzQ9j\">pic.twitter.com/a6s4WbzQ9j</a></p>&mdash; Jon Schwabish (@jschwabish) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jschwabish/status/1552734204936523776?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">July 28, 2022</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A workaround to show the axis on the right side of the chart in Tableau is to copy your measure and create a <a href=\"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/multiple_measures.htm#compare-two-measures-using-dual-axes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">dual-axis</a>. A downside of this approach is that Tableau also duplicates all the marks in the view, which &#8211; if you have a complicated view &#8211; could lead to a longer load time.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tableau Visionary, Sam Parsons, raised this issue on twitter, below, and provided a <a href=\"https://community.tableau.com/s/idea/0878b000000My37AAC/detail\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">link to an idea</a> on the Tableau Forums, which I’d encourage you to upvote. The discussion in the below thread is also worth reading.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"embed-twitter\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Hey hey <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/DataFam?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#DataFam</a>,<br><br>Please upvote my <a href=\"https://twitter.com/tableau?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@tableau</a> Idea I have just submitted.<br><br>Link: <a href=\"https://t.co/ikS8X7nEKF\">https://t.co/ikS8X7nEKF</a><br><br>In a nut shell:  &quot;Allow the user more flexibility on where and when the axis are shown&quot;<br><br>Stop the dual axis workarounds, that duplicate marks.<br>Make this in-built options. <a href=\"https://t.co/cd11tqGh8R\">pic.twitter.com/cd11tqGh8R</a></p>&mdash; Sam Parsons (@SParsonsDataViz) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SParsonsDataViz/status/1573246339449757697?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">September 23, 2022</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Below are two methods for creating the dual-axis without duplicating the marks.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Create a NULL measure in the same data source</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the original scatterplot view with 5,111 marks (as shown on the lower left corner in the status bar):</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3248\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/00-original-view/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png\" data-orig-size=\"1097,671\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"00-original-view\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png?w=1097\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3248\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png 1097w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/00-original-view.png?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1097px) 100vw, 1097px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>First, create a new calculation:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>INT(NULL)</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3250\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/01-null-calc/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/01-null-calc.png\" data-orig-size=\"489,301\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"01-null-calc\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/01-null-calc.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/01-null-calc.png?w=489\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/01-null-calc.png?w=489\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3250\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/01-null-calc.png 489w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/01-null-calc.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/01-null-calc.png?w=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 489px) 100vw, 489px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This calculation can then be added to the view next to your original measure, here I’m using it on both Rows and Columns for this scatterplot:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3249\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/03-null-dual-axis/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png\" data-orig-size=\"1097,671\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"03-null-dual-axis\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png?w=1097\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3249\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png 1097w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/03-null-dual-axis.png?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1097px) 100vw, 1097px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, select dual-axis from the context menu of each NULL pill:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3251\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/02-dual-axis-option/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/02-dual-axis-option.png\" data-orig-size=\"448,430\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"02-dual-axis-option\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/02-dual-axis-option.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/02-dual-axis-option.png?w=448\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/02-dual-axis-option.png?w=448\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3251\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/02-dual-axis-option.png 448w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/02-dual-axis-option.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/02-dual-axis-option.png?w=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 448px) 100vw, 448px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will result in axes on all four sides of the scatter plot but the values on the NULL axes will not align. Note, doing this will also add <strong>Measure Names </strong>to the Colour shelf so remove this as it’s not needed.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3252\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/04-dual-axis-scatterplot/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png\" data-orig-size=\"1097,671\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"04-dual-axis-scatterplot\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png?w=1097\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3252\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png 1097w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/04-dual-axis-scatterplot.png?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1097px) 100vw, 1097px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To fix that, right-click on the axis and select <strong>Synchronise Axis </strong>(do this for both the NULL axes):</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3253\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/05-sync-axes/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/05-sync-axes.png\" data-orig-size=\"624,340\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"05-sync-axes\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/05-sync-axes.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/05-sync-axes.png?w=624\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/05-sync-axes.png?w=624\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3253\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/05-sync-axes.png 624w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/05-sync-axes.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/05-sync-axes.png?w=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 624px) 100vw, 624px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The NULL axes will update to match the values on the respective pills they have a dual-axis with:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3254\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/06-sync-axes-result/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/06-sync-axes-result.png\" data-orig-size=\"722,528\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"06-sync-axes-result\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/06-sync-axes-result.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/06-sync-axes-result.png?w=722\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/06-sync-axes-result.png?w=722\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3254\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/06-sync-axes-result.png 722w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/06-sync-axes-result.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/06-sync-axes-result.png?w=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 722px) 100vw, 722px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The NULL axes can then be renamed or the name removed by right-clicking on them and selecting <strong>Edit Axis… </strong>and making the required changes. Here I’ve removed the axis labels. I’ve also hidden the Null values indicator in the lower-right hand corner by right-clicking on it and selecting <strong>Hide Indicator</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3255\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/07-null-values-hide-indicator/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/07-null-values-hide-indicator.png\" data-orig-size=\"170,79\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"07-null-values-hide-indicator\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/07-null-values-hide-indicator.png?w=170\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/07-null-values-hide-indicator.png?w=170\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/07-null-values-hide-indicator.png?w=170\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3255\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/07-null-values-hide-indicator.png 170w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/07-null-values-hide-indicator.png?w=150 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 170px) 100vw, 170px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3264\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/08-cleaned-view-1/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/08-cleaned-view-1.png\" data-orig-size=\"639,437\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"08-cleaned-view-1\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/08-cleaned-view-1.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/08-cleaned-view-1.png?w=639\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/08-cleaned-view-1.png?w=639\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3264\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/08-cleaned-view-1.png 639w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/08-cleaned-view-1.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/08-cleaned-view-1.png?w=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, 639px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This approach will create a new column in your data source with a NULL value on every row:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3257\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/09-null-column/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/09-null-column.png\" data-orig-size=\"703,497\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"09-null-column\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/09-null-column.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/09-null-column.png?w=703\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/09-null-column.png?w=703\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3257\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/09-null-column.png 703w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/09-null-column.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/09-null-column.png?w=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 703px) 100vw, 703px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’d rather not have this column, see the second option below:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Blend with a dummy data source</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This option gives you access to the NULL value to perform the same operations as above but the NULL comes from a second data source.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Copy the below two lines and paste them into Tableau:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>Dummy<br>NULL</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>This will create a clipboard data source containing one row of data &#8211; the NULL value:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3258\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/10-dummy-data-source/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png\" data-orig-size=\"874,670\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"10-dummy-data-source\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png?w=874\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3258\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png 874w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/10-dummy-data-source.png?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 874px) 100vw, 874px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If the value is showing as a Dimension in the Data Pane, right-click on it and select <strong>Convert to Measure</strong>. You may also need to change the data type to integer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can now follow the steps from the prior example, adding the dummy measure to the view, dual axis, synchronise etc. Here is the first step &#8211; notice how an orange tick has appeared to indicate that blending is taking place:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3260\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/11-blending/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png\" data-orig-size=\"968,671\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"11-blending\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png?w=968\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3260\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png 968w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/11-blending.png?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 968px) 100vw, 968px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As we are not linking on any fields, there isn’t actually a meaningful blend taking place but it doesn’t matter in this use case as we are not using a meaningful value, just getting access to the NULL value from a separate source. You can learn more about blends on <a href=\"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/multiple_connections.htm\">this help page</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below is the final view using the blend approach, again, still showing 5,111 marks.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3261\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2022/09/26/creating-multiple-axes-without-duplicating-marks/12-final-blend/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png\" data-orig-size=\"968,671\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"12-final-blend\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png?w=968\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3261\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png 968w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2022/09/12-final-blend.png?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 968px) 100vw, 968px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This approach does not create a Null column in your main data source:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/CbobqFLIw0Bo-NQXAU78T2MyTaqm3gzti0Thi3drXyUVRFkAwf3ivnDLRdUTzZNt64cBMdlSvENpXZlgRniTAFLAooooMt2TiTGoe1d2PM70pIHzQAT6-F-WbenM5acwQmyDKYyNj-FF8n1CfUCN-8iPJ7yR38jk9nFph233K4eK54fmsD3_WB7OAA\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I hope this was useful. Please don’t forget to upvote <a href=\"https://community.tableau.com/s/idea/0878b000000My37AAC/detail\">Sam’s idea</a> for providing more flexibility and control over axes in Tableau!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thanks,<br>Marc&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-social-links has-icon-color has-icon-background-color is-style-default is-content-justification-left is-layout-flex wp-container-9\"><li style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000; \" class=\"wp-social-link wp-social-link-twitter wp-block-social-link\"><a rel=\" noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/datavisblog\" class=\"wp-block-social-link-anchor\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.1\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><path d=\"M22.23,5.924c-0.736,0.326-1.527,0.547-2.357,0.646c0.847-0.508,1.498-1.312,1.804-2.27 c-0.793,0.47-1.671,0.812-2.606,0.996C18.324,4.498,17.257,4,16.077,4c-2.266,0-4.103,1.837-4.103,4.103 c0,0.322,0.036,0.635,0.106,0.935C8.67,8.867,5.647,7.234,3.623,4.751C3.27,5.357,3.067,6.062,3.067,6.814 c0,1.424,0.724,2.679,1.825,3.415c-0.673-0.021-1.305-0.20